ench environmental movement. Survival emerges as the organizing concept for a variety of democratic political forms that center the corporeality of desire in social movements contesting the expanding management of life by state institutions across the globe. Vigilant and timely, balancing fine-tuned analysis with broad historical overview to map the utopian impulse across contemporary cultural and political life, Chrostowska issues an urgent report on the vitality of utopia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCritical theory. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 0aUtopias. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Utopias.2bisacsh  aBody Politics.  aBody Utopia.  aClimate Crisis.  aCritical Theory.  aHistory of Political Ideas (20th Century to the Present).  aRadical Political Thought.  aRadical Social Theory.  aUtopianism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishz978311075417908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021z9783110753943oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073914540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363000040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503630000423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503630000/original  a978-3-11-073914-5  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075417-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2021 Englishb2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-PLWb2021